# creating train and test data with 75/25 split

split <- initial_split(listings, prop = 0.75)

listings_train <- training(split)
listings_test <- testing(split)

# dim of each split
dim(listings_train) 
## [1] 5625   13

## [1] 1875   13

recipe <- recipe(price ~ ., data = listings) %>%
  step_YeoJohnson(all_numeric_predictors()) %>%
  step_novel(all_nominal_predictors()) %>%
  #creates dummy variables out of all factor variables/predictors
  step_dummy(all_nominal_predictors()) %>%
  #removes predictors with little or no information
  step_nzv(all_numeric_predictors()) %>%
  step_corr(all_numeric_predictors()) %>%
  step_lincomb()

recipe
## 
##  Recipe 
## 
##  Inputs
## Number of variables by role
## outcome:    1
## predictor: 12
## 
##  Operations
##  Yeo-Johnson transformation on: all_numeric_predictors()
##  Novel factor level assignment for: all_nominal_predictors()
##  Dummy variables from: all_nominal_predictors()
##  Sparse, unbalanced variable filter on: all_numeric_predictors()
##  Correlation filter on: all_numeric_predictors()
##  Linear combination filter on: <none>
#setup model
lr_model <- linear_reg() %>%
  set_engine("lm") %>%
  set_mode("regression")

lr_model
## Linear Regression Model Specification (regression)
## 
## Computational engine: lm

#setup workflow
lr_workflow <- workflow() %>%
  add_recipe(recipe) %>%
  add_model(lr_model)
#fitting the model
lr_fit <-
  lr_workflow %>%
  fit(data = listings_train)


extracted_fit <- lr_fit %>%
  extract_fit_parsnip()

summary(extracted_fit$fit)

# set up glmnet model
listings_glmnet <- linear_reg(
  engine = "glmnet",
  mixture = tune(),
  penalty = tune()
)


# set up glmnet workflow
listings_glmnet_workflow <- workflow() %>%
  add_recipe(recipe) %>%
  add_model(listings_glmnet)

#set up grid
glmnet_grid <- grid_regular(
  penalty(),
  mixture(), 
  levels = 10
)

# five cv
set.seed(42)  
folds <- vfold_cv(listings_train, v = 10)


#tune
tune_glmnet_results <- tune_grid(    
  listings_glmnet_workflow,
  resamples = folds,
  grid = glmnet_grid
)


# see best params
best_params_glmnet <- select_best(tune_glmnet_results, metric = "rmse")
best_params_glmnet


#finalize using best cv params
final_glmnet_workflow <- finalize_workflow(listings_glmnet_workflow, best_params_glmnet)


#fit final workflow
fit_final_glmnet_workflow <- 
  final_glmnet_workflow %>%
  fit(data = listings_train)

#show coefficients in fit model 

fit_final_glmnet_workflow %>% 
  tidy() %>% 
  select(term, estimate)

holdout_glmnet_preds <- fit_final_glmnet_workflow %>% 
  predict(new_data = holdout_x) %>% 
  bind_cols(holdout_x) %>%
select(id, price = .pred)

write.csv(holdout_glmnet_preds,"glmnet.csv", row.names = FALSE)

#nnet

nnet <- mlp(
  mode = "regression",
  hidden_units = tune()
)


nnet_workflow <- workflow() %>%
  add_recipe(recipe) %>%
  add_model(nnet)

nnet_grid <- grid_regular(
  hidden_units(), 
  levels = 5
)

folds <- vfold_cv(listings_train, v = 5)


nnet_results <- tune_grid(
  nnet_workflow, 
  resamples = folds, 
  grid = nnet_grid,
  control = control_grid(verbose = TRUE)
)
